windows.question:
Which of the following best describes the anomaly detection results within the time series window spanning steps 1562 to 1578?
A) Sudden Decrease anomaly: Values experience a rapid decline that fails to match nearby gradual behavior.
B) Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.
C) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.

options.A: Sudden Decrease anomaly: Values experience a rapid decline that fails to match nearby gradual behavior.
options.B: Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.
options.C: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.

windows.answer: B) Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.

windows.question:

A) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
B) Shake anomaly: The time series exhibits sudden, uncharacteristic fluctuations.
C) Downward Spike anomaly: Values plunge dramatically in a sudden downward spike.

options.A: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
options.B: Shake anomaly: The time series exhibits sudden, uncharacteristic fluctuations.
options.C: Downward Spike anomaly: Values plunge dramatically in a sudden downward spike.

windows.answer: A) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
